entries.body:
LaTeX is used for document preparation and typesetting — especially in academia, for scientific and mathematical documents.

The injection arises wherever user input ends up in a LaTeX document that is then compiled on the server (generating a PDF from LaTeX):
• online formula and LaTeX document editors;
• PDF generators — reports, invoices, diplomas, resumes, certificates;
• fields rendered into the final PDF (name, title, signature, comment).

Thanks to LaTeX's powerful scripting capabilities, it allows reading/writing files and executing commands if the compilation is not sandboxed.
